"title": "5166: liver and kidneys",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5166: liver and kidneys",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>The liver and kidneys as vital internal organs of the body</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:23\">PRO 7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:13\">JOB 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:24-Job20:25\">JOB 20:24–20:25</a></p>\n<h2>The liver and kidneys are symbolic of human emotions and the conscience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:21\">PSA 73:21</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew words for liver and kidneys are occasionally translated as “heart”, “spirit” or “inmost being”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:27\">JOB 19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:16\">PRO 23:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:2\">JER 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:11\">LAM 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:13\">LAM 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>God examines the innermost being as symbolised by the kidneys</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:2\">PSA 26:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:9\">PSA 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:20\">JER 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:10\">JER 17:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:12\">JER 20:12</a></p>\n<h3>God is concerned for the innermost being as symbolised by the kidneys</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:13\">PSA 139:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:7\">PSA 16:7</a></p>\n<h2>The liver and kidneys as offered in animal sacrifice</h2>\n<h3>Liver and kidneys offered in various sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:3-Lev3:5\">LEV 3:3–3:5</a></strong> <em>The liver and kidneys are associated with the fat as the choice parts of the animal.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:9-Lev3:11\">LEV 3:9–3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:14-Lev3:16\">LEV 3:14–3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:8-Lev4:10\">LEV 4:8–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:3-Lev7:6\">LEV 7:3–7:6</a></p>\n<h3>Liver and kidneys had a central role in the ordination services for priests</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:13\">EXO 29:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:22-Exod29:25\">EXO 29:22–29:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:16-Lev8:17\">LEV 8:16–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:25-Lev8:28\">LEV 8:25–8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:8-Lev9:10\">LEV 9:8–9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:19-Lev9:21\">LEV 9:19–9:21</a></p>\n<h2>Divination by inspection of the liver</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:21\">EZK 21:21</a> <em>Divination by inspection of the liver (hepatoscopy) was a common practice. The future was predicted from the colour and configuration of the liver of a sacrificial animal, usually a sheep.</em></p>",
